<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="b1940_07_26_an_SraffaPiero"><teiHeader><fileDesc> <titleStmt> <title>Von <persName key="WittgensteinLudwig" role="sender" full="yes">Ludwig Wittgenstein</persName> an <persName key="SraffaPiero" role="recipient" full="yes">Piero Sraffa</persName>, 26. 7. 1940</title> <author>Wittgenstein, Ludwig</author> </titleStmt> <editionStmt n="bw2"> <edition>2. Auflage</edition> </editionStmt> <publicationStmt> <p>Ludwig Wittgenstein: Gesamtbriefwechsel, 2. Auflage</p> </publicationStmt> <sourceDesc default="false"> <p>Abschrift McGuinness, Kopie in BA.  Publiziert (WiC, S. 328).</p> </sourceDesc> </fileDesc><encodingDesc><p>TEI P5</p></encodingDesc><revisionDesc><list type="simple"><item>2010/05/15: Added to the collection</item><item>2018/12: Added to Innsbruck Correspondence Edition</item></list></revisionDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div type="transcript" org="uniform" part="N" sample="complete"> <div type="address" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="right">Trinity College </p> <p rend="right">Cambridge </p> <p rend="right">26.7.40. </p> </div> <div type="maintext" org="uniform" sample="complete" part="N"> <p rend="left">Dear Sraffa,</p> <p rend="indent">I’ve had a book seller send you “The thin man”, a detective story, I told you about a few months ago. Read it &amp; don’t be ashamed of liking it even though you know that I liked it. I’ve seen your mother several times. She looks well &amp; didn’t seem a bit depressed.</p> <p rend="indent">Hutt has been called up.</p> <p rend="indent">I had quite good news from my sister in New York.</p> <p rend="indent">I am &amp; feel just as usual.</p> <p rend="indent">Yours </p> <p rend="indent">Ludwig Wittgenstein </p> </div> </div></body></text></TEI>